#: options-admin.php:213
msgid ""
"By default, attributes passed from your Shibboleth Service Provider will be accessed using standard environment variables.\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\tFor most users, leaving these defaults is perfectly fine. If you are running a special server configuration that results in environment variables\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\tbeing sent with the prefix <code>REDIRECT_</code>, you should select the \"Redirected Environment Variables\" option. If you are running\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\tyour Shibboleth Service Provider on a reverse proxy, you should select the \"HTTP Headers\" option and, if at all possible, add a spoofkey below.\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\tIf you are running Shibboleth with a custom prefix, you should select the \"Custom Prefix\" option and complete the \"Custom Attribute Access Prefix\" field that appears below."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:227
msgid "Custom Attribute Access Prefix"
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:233
msgid ""
"If you wish to use a custom attribute access prefix, enter it here. This field is case-insensitive.\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\t<br /><b>WARNING:</b> If you incorrectly set this option, you will force <b><i>ALL</i></b> attempts to authenticate with Shibboleth to fail."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:244
msgid "Spoof Key"
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:250
msgid ""
"For more details on setting a spoof key on the Shibboleth Service Provider, see <a href=\"https://wiki.shibboleth.net/confluence/display/SHIB2/NativeSPSpoofChecking\">this wiki document</a>.\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\t<br /><b>WARNING:</b> If you incorrectly set this option, you will force <b><i>ALL</i></b> attempts to authenticate with Shibboleth to fail."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:261
msgid "Enable Fallback Attribute Access"
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:264
msgid "Allow the standard environment variables to be used as a fallback for attribute access."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:268
msgid ""
"If set, this will fallback to standard environment variables when the selected\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t attribute access method fails."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:278
msgid "Default Login Method"
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:281
msgid "Use Shibboleth as the default login method for users."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:285
msgid ""
"If set, this will cause all standard WordPress login links to initiate Shibboleth\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t login instead of local WordPress authentication.  Shibboleth login can always be\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t initiated from the WordPress login form by clicking the \"Log in with Shibboleth\" link."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:296
msgid "Automatic Login"
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:299
msgid "Use Shibboleth to auto-login users."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:304
msgid ""
"If set, this option checks to see if a Shibboleth session exists on every page load, and,\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\tif it does, forces a <code>wp_signon()</code> call and <code>wp_safe_redirect()</code> back to the <code>$_SERVER['REQUEST_URI']</code>."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:315
msgid "Disable Local Authentication"
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:318
msgid "Disables local WordPress authentication."
msgstr ""

#: options-admin.php:322
msgid ""
"<b>WARNING:</b> Disabling local authentication can potentially lock you out of WordPress if you have misconfigured the plugin or have a non-functional Shibboleth Service Provider.\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t\tMake sure that you are confident your configuration is functional before enabling this option."
msgstr ""

